WEBVTT

00:00:14.990 --> 00:00:18.990
Arima Kinen

00:00:24.680 --> 00:00:26.070
One more race...

00:00:26.380 --> 00:00:30.160
Up next is my last race
in the Twinkle Series.

00:00:39.040 --> 00:00:40.530
Her time's holding up.

00:00:44.410 --> 00:00:49.270
She's running like she's ready to
burn herself all the way out.

00:00:57.290 --> 00:00:58.880
I'm going for another.

00:00:58.880 --> 00:01:00.100
Crown-san?

00:01:04.960 --> 00:01:06.340
Work hard.

00:01:08.070 --> 00:01:11.060
Kitasan is working real hard again!

00:01:11.060 --> 00:01:15.300
She'd have regrets if she didn't
manage to win in the end.

00:01:15.300 --> 00:01:16.630
So she's fighting hard.

00:01:16.840 --> 00:01:18.760
You're not gonna be outdone
though, huh, Chevacchi?

00:01:19.520 --> 00:01:20.490
Of course not.

00:01:23.730 --> 00:01:25.530
You okay, Kitasan?

00:01:25.530 --> 00:01:27.550
Yes! All good!

00:01:27.980 --> 00:01:31.110
That'll do for today.
Cool down and wrap it up.

00:01:31.710 --> 00:01:34.370
Right! Thank you so much!

00:01:40.760 --> 00:01:43.290
I wish we could do something for Kitasan.

00:01:43.290 --> 00:01:45.540
Yeah, I wish we could.

00:01:43.810 --> 00:01:47.810
Episode 13
\hAnd Yours...

00:01:45.540 --> 00:01:47.290
It'd be nice if we could do something.

00:01:47.290 --> 00:01:48.550
It would be.

00:01:48.550 --> 00:01:49.980
If only there was something.

00:01:49.980 --> 00:01:51.570
We gotta be able to do something.

00:01:54.100 --> 00:01:55.260
Hello, everyone.

00:01:55.260 --> 00:01:57.450
Welcome back, Kitasan.

00:01:57.450 --> 00:01:59.530
Here you are. A custom drink.

00:01:59.530 --> 00:02:01.130
Specially made yet again!

00:02:01.670 --> 00:02:02.890
Thank you!

00:02:03.920 --> 00:02:06.390
You've been looking out
for me every day lately.

00:02:06.390 --> 00:02:07.860
There's no need to start getting bashful.

00:02:07.860 --> 00:02:09.900
That's right! We want to help.

00:02:10.910 --> 00:02:11.970
Everyone...

00:02:13.100 --> 00:02:17.400
I'm so glad I joined Spica.

00:02:20.640 --> 00:02:23.160
Is there anything specific we can do for you?

00:02:24.930 --> 00:02:26.090
Since you asked...

00:02:27.160 --> 00:02:30.100
I just thought of something.

00:02:31.280 --> 00:02:33.380
Did you see the preliminary
results of the fan vote?

00:02:33.380 --> 00:02:36.300
I sure did. Kitasan Black had an early lead.

00:02:36.300 --> 00:02:39.230
I mean, yeah, if you think
about it, of course she does.

00:02:36.300 --> 00:02:39.230
Arima Kinen

00:02:39.230 --> 00:02:41.760
Twinkle 12
Our Arima Kinen Feature
Kitasan Black's Last Run!

00:02:39.230 --> 00:02:42.810
At both the Takarazuka and Arima,
she always gets picked in the fan vote,

00:02:41.760 --> 00:02:44.600
Kitasan Black’s Hopes for
Victory at the Arima Kinen

00:02:42.810 --> 00:02:44.600
but just can't seem to
score a Grand Prix win.

00:02:44.600 --> 00:02:48.600
Kitasan Black in Great Condition!!

00:02:44.600 --> 00:02:48.600
Will her hard training take her
straight to the top at Arima?!

00:02:44.890 --> 00:02:47.140
Even though she's won
plenty of G1 races before.

00:02:47.140 --> 00:02:49.100
I hope she can pull it off in the end.

00:02:49.100 --> 00:02:52.330
I know she'll take the
Arima Kinen! It's Kitasan!

00:02:52.330 --> 00:02:54.440
She seems to be in pretty
good condition, too.

00:02:54.440 --> 00:02:56.370
The Japan Cup was a close race.

00:02:56.370 --> 00:02:58.870
Yeah, she was passed at the very end,

00:02:58.870 --> 00:03:01.960
but up until that point, she was running
away like Kitasan usually does.

00:03:01.960 --> 00:03:05.270
Still, her wrapping it up after
this... I'm going to miss her.

00:03:05.270 --> 00:03:06.080
I know what you mean!

00:03:06.080 --> 00:03:09.310
Since it's the last time, it feels
like I can't miss it, no matter what.

00:03:09.750 --> 00:03:12.970
Right? Let's cheer loud so that
we don't have any regrets.

00:03:12.970 --> 00:03:14.000
You betcha!

00:03:14.000 --> 00:03:17.370
My husband and I are heading to
the Nakayama Racecourse for it.

00:03:17.370 --> 00:03:19.230
Oh dear, so are we!

00:03:19.230 --> 00:03:21.690
Nothing beats seeing it in person, after all.

00:03:22.220 --> 00:03:27.060
My husband's actually been rewatching all
of Kitasan's races starting with her debut!

00:03:27.060 --> 00:03:29.560
Oh, my, so has mine!

00:03:29.560 --> 00:03:31.640
Who do you think is gonna be
favored to win on the day of?

00:03:31.640 --> 00:03:35.020
I mean, come on, who else could it be?

00:03:35.020 --> 00:03:36.300
I know, right?

00:03:36.300 --> 00:03:38.960
I'm sure she's gonna enjoy
the taste of victory.

00:03:38.960 --> 00:03:41.150
I bet she can, knowing Kitasan.

00:03:41.360 --> 00:03:44.010
Daddy, can Kita-chan win?

00:03:44.010 --> 00:03:46.200
Yeah. I think she can.

00:03:46.200 --> 00:03:48.500
She's been working really
hard so that she can.

00:03:48.500 --> 00:03:51.540
Then I'm gonna work real
hard and cheer for her!

00:04:03.420 --> 00:04:09.380
A scene that's like a festival... what I've
yearned for and always dreamed about.

00:04:10.320 --> 00:04:14.330
That view that I was so
close to making happen.

00:04:16.470 --> 00:04:17.760
But I couldn't realize it.

00:04:18.650 --> 00:04:22.630
Still, I'm going to show
the best race possible

00:04:22.630 --> 00:04:24.950
to the people who've always supported me.

00:04:25.710 --> 00:04:29.310
So that they see me off with a smile.

00:04:29.310 --> 00:04:30.540
Kita-chan!

00:04:33.830 --> 00:04:35.150
Teio-san?

00:04:35.150 --> 00:04:36.310
Good work out there.

00:04:37.130 --> 00:04:40.430
Everyone's really excited
about the thing you asked for.

00:04:40.960 --> 00:04:42.430
I appreciate it!

00:04:45.260 --> 00:04:46.410
It's finally time, huh?

00:04:47.250 --> 00:04:49.710
Yes. It finally is.

00:04:52.900 --> 00:04:55.460
I want to win.

00:04:57.110 --> 00:05:00.150
More than anything, with this being the end.

00:05:04.070 --> 00:05:07.910
I see. I think it's the
same for everyone, though.

00:05:08.250 --> 00:05:10.910
Nobody's racing to lose.

00:05:10.910 --> 00:05:12.910
But only one gets to win.

00:05:14.170 --> 00:05:18.360
Still, I think the winner is the one who,

00:05:18.360 --> 00:05:23.170
no matter how tough or painful it gets,
keeps working hard to the very end.

00:05:25.400 --> 00:05:27.500
And I've been watching you—

00:05:27.500 --> 00:05:31.630
Kita-chan who never gives up,
no matter what—all this time!

00:05:32.370 --> 00:05:33.740
Teio-san...

00:05:36.970 --> 00:05:37.710
Right.

00:05:41.400 --> 00:05:44.490
The end of the year looms as
we're here on Christmas Eve.

00:05:42.460 --> 00:05:45.900
Arima Kinen
Nakayama               Turf\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h

00:05:44.490 --> 00:05:46.660
And as festive spirits fill the town,

00:05:46.660 --> 00:05:49.910
here at Nakayama Racecourse,
it's time for the Arima Kinen.

00:05:50.230 --> 00:05:53.160
We've got a remarkable lineup
of runners again this year.

00:05:53.160 --> 00:05:58.390
But who will walk away with the glory
of winning this year's final Grand Prix?

00:05:58.390 --> 00:05:59.170
It comes every year,

00:05:59.170 --> 00:06:00.410
and every year, it's an exciting race.

00:06:00.410 --> 00:06:01.830
It certainly is.

00:06:01.830 --> 00:06:06.730
I'm sure even the audience watching
the footage from our cameras

00:06:06.730 --> 00:06:09.140
can sense the intensity and
excitement from the stands.

00:06:11.120 --> 00:06:14.600
I'm coming to you live from in front
of the paddocks at Nakayama Racecourse!

00:06:14.600 --> 00:06:16.350
Yep!

00:06:16.760 --> 00:06:22.840
But which horse girl will be delivering
victory in lieu of a present from Santa

00:06:22.840 --> 00:06:24.450
to these over 100,000 spectators?

00:06:24.930 --> 00:06:26.390
It won't be long now.

00:06:26.390 --> 00:06:28.320
It's nearly time to race.

00:06:29.660 --> 00:06:32.660
Green Room

00:06:35.160 --> 00:06:38.400
K-Kita-san, you look amazing!

00:06:38.400 --> 00:06:39.670
I'm so glad.

00:06:39.880 --> 00:06:41.290
It suits you wonderfully.

00:06:43.930 --> 00:06:46.670
Thank you all so much.

00:06:47.190 --> 00:06:49.360
There's something refreshing
about seeing you in shorts.

00:06:49.360 --> 00:06:51.410
Pretty slick, huh? Easy to run in, too.

00:06:51.410 --> 00:06:53.900
The cape was my idea.

00:06:53.900 --> 00:06:55.920
The sash is an elegant addition.

00:06:55.920 --> 00:06:57.720
It makes you come across as a leader.

00:06:57.720 --> 00:07:00.090
Pretty good, right? That one was all me!

00:07:00.090 --> 00:07:03.890
I don't see my idea anywhere!

00:07:01.970 --> 00:07:04.510
I'm really glad I asked you all for this.

00:07:04.510 --> 00:07:07.780
I'm going to run my last race
carrying Spica's sentiments.

00:07:04.520 --> 00:07:07.780
But my idea...

00:07:08.000 --> 00:07:11.280
Man, I wish I had that idea.

00:07:11.280 --> 00:07:13.060
None of that, now.

00:07:13.060 --> 00:07:16.330
This might sound weird, but come
back without getting hurt, all right?

00:07:16.330 --> 00:07:17.280
Right.

00:07:17.650 --> 00:07:19.710
Well, I'm heading off.

00:07:23.040 --> 00:07:25.380
Now, on the turf, we can see the runners

00:07:25.380 --> 00:07:28.390
in tense anticipation for
the beginning of the race.

00:07:28.960 --> 00:07:31.180
There's Sounds of Earth,

00:07:31.180 --> 00:07:34.650
with three second-place G1 finishes
and four second-place G2 wins,

00:07:34.650 --> 00:07:36.230
who always seems to be
verging on a breakthrough.

00:07:36.230 --> 00:07:38.810
Regardless of her other races recently,

00:07:38.810 --> 00:07:41.980
it'd be great to see her first G1 victory
here at Arima at the end of the year.

00:07:41.980 --> 00:07:44.040
Get 'em, Earth!

00:07:44.040 --> 00:07:47.320
From the looks of things,
she's certainly relaxed.

00:07:47.320 --> 00:07:48.650
Mm-hmm!

00:07:48.650 --> 00:07:51.730
The Arima Kinen. The bookend
race for an entire year.

00:07:51.730 --> 00:07:54.320
And on top of that, today is
Kitasan Black's last run.

00:07:54.770 --> 00:07:56.860
There's an unmatched level
of attention on this race.

00:07:56.860 --> 00:07:59.550
It's an ideal chance to
make a mark on history.

00:07:59.550 --> 00:08:02.330
You can do this. I know you can, Earth-san!

00:08:05.850 --> 00:08:09.590
Speaking of first G1 victories,
here we someone who's been elevated

00:08:09.590 --> 00:08:12.700
to a new level by winning
the Japan Cup, Cheval Grand.

00:08:12.700 --> 00:08:15.260
Will we see the return of the
razor-sharp acceleration that

00:08:15.260 --> 00:08:16.600
brought home that victory?

00:08:17.080 --> 00:08:20.380
I'd also keep an eye on Satono Crown,
who won the Takarazuka Kinen this year.

00:08:20.380 --> 00:08:23.910
Will she able to avenge her loss
at the last race here at Nakayama?

00:08:24.370 --> 00:08:26.190
You can do this, Crown-san!

00:08:27.740 --> 00:08:32.220
Then we have the heavily-favored
number one in the fan vote...

00:08:32.220 --> 00:08:34.570
The star horse girl of this year,

00:08:34.570 --> 00:08:36.630
and someone whose win today
would rank her among those

00:08:36.630 --> 00:08:38.760
with the most G1 wins: Kitasan Black!

00:08:38.760 --> 00:08:42.810
Today is her last run. I only hope
she'll come away with no regrets.

00:08:43.500 --> 00:08:46.830
This is the last time I
run in the Twinkle Series.

00:08:50.650 --> 00:08:54.490
My last time feeling the tension
and anxiety before we start.

00:08:56.460 --> 00:08:58.600
And now, it's time to begin.

00:08:58.600 --> 00:09:00.250
The culmination of the past 12 months,

00:09:00.250 --> 00:09:03.100
the grand prix that closes
the year, the Arima Kinen!

00:09:33.230 --> 00:09:36.730
Underneath a wintry sky, we see the
horse girls enter the gate one by one

00:09:36.730 --> 00:09:39.040
with smoldering passion in their hearts.

00:10:06.810 --> 00:10:11.050
The stage is set for the end-of-the-year
grand prix, the Arima Kinen.

00:10:17.010 --> 00:10:21.010
Umamusume

00:10:17.010 --> 00:10:21.010
Pretty Derby

00:10:21.450 --> 00:10:25.670
And they're off! Kitasan Black
has a good start!

00:10:25.670 --> 00:10:29.420
Kitasan Black takes the
initiative on the inside,

00:10:29.420 --> 00:10:31.740
but there are still 2,500 meters to go!

00:10:31.740 --> 00:10:35.390
Kitasan Black has the lead heading into
the four sharp corners of Nakayama,

00:10:35.390 --> 00:10:37.650
entering the first and
approaching the second!

00:10:37.650 --> 00:10:39.290
Off to a good start!

00:10:39.290 --> 00:10:40.010
She is!

00:10:40.010 --> 00:10:41.710
Hell yeah, keep it up!

00:10:41.710 --> 00:10:43.160
Good luck, Kitasan!

00:10:45.330 --> 00:10:46.810
Kitasan Black holds the lead.

00:10:46.810 --> 00:10:50.960
In second place is Xbalanque, followed by
the veteran horse girl Canon Mille-feuille,

00:10:50.960 --> 00:10:52.830
and then Crescent Ace on the inside,

00:10:52.830 --> 00:10:57.500
It's Calling behind her,
with Lead Poetry on her tail.

00:10:57.500 --> 00:10:59.420
Sounds of Earth is bringing up the rear.

00:10:59.420 --> 00:11:02.450
And now, these 16 courageous racers
cross in front of the stands!

00:11:02.450 --> 00:11:04.640
This is what the fans have been waiting for!

00:11:04.640 --> 00:11:06.680
This is the last run for Kitasan Black!

00:11:08.890 --> 00:11:12.440
As she crosses the turf screen, it seems
like she's checking the scoreboard.

00:11:12.440 --> 00:11:14.810
How is the race flowing?
How's the pace evolving?

00:11:14.810 --> 00:11:16.440
Is she running it on her own terms?

00:11:16.440 --> 00:11:19.700
The first 1,000 meters are
crossed in 61.6 seconds!

00:11:19.700 --> 00:11:21.430
Nice, she's setting a good pace.

00:11:21.430 --> 00:11:22.290
She is!

00:11:22.290 --> 00:11:24.470
She saw the opening and is
running on her own terms!

00:11:24.470 --> 00:11:25.320
She is!

00:11:25.320 --> 00:11:26.910
But she looks like she's struggling, too.

00:11:26.910 --> 00:11:28.010
She is?!

00:11:29.450 --> 00:11:31.520
If I relax for a second...

00:11:31.520 --> 00:11:33.380
If I fall one step behind...

00:11:33.380 --> 00:11:35.000
If I let them catch up...

00:11:38.140 --> 00:11:38.880
Which is why—

00:11:40.110 --> 00:11:43.680
I guess today's the last day we
get to watch Kita-chan like this.

00:11:43.930 --> 00:11:46.350
I wish it could go on forever.

00:11:46.350 --> 00:11:50.180
Kita-chan's really become
a part of our daily lives.

00:11:50.180 --> 00:11:52.120
Let's make sure we remember every bit of it.

00:11:52.120 --> 00:11:54.190
You can get misty-eyed later!

00:11:54.190 --> 00:11:57.800
Kita-chan's running with all she's got!
So we're gonna cheer just the same!

00:11:59.110 --> 00:12:00.320
We sure are.

00:12:05.100 --> 00:12:08.810
Things are shaping up ideally for
Kitasan Black here on her last run.

00:12:08.810 --> 00:12:13.120
Xbalanque holds in second place, with her
eyes set on a chance to usurp victory.

00:12:13.120 --> 00:12:14.960
Crescent Ace is on the inside,

00:12:14.960 --> 00:12:17.960
with Canon Mille-feuille poking
her head in from the outside.

00:12:17.960 --> 00:12:21.470
Followed by It's Calling and
Read Poetry on the outside.

00:12:21.470 --> 00:12:24.600
Chronicle Oath is on the inside,
with Black Ebony in the middle of the pack.

00:12:24.600 --> 00:12:27.170
On the outside, we can see
Cheval Grand's position.

00:12:27.170 --> 00:12:29.750
The Japan Cup winner is holding steady.

00:12:29.750 --> 00:12:32.440
Behind her is the Takarazuka
grand prix winner,

00:12:32.440 --> 00:12:35.230
Satono Crown, and on the
outside is Ribbon Etude!

00:12:35.880 --> 00:12:39.020
Kitasan Black, I'm going to beat you again!

00:12:39.020 --> 00:12:41.550
I'm going to win both grand prix!

00:12:41.550 --> 00:12:45.450
Once you leave the turf,
I'll still be racing!

00:12:45.450 --> 00:12:49.260
On the inside we have
Original Sign, Seventh Queen,

00:12:49.260 --> 00:12:51.850
and pushing up from the
rear is Sounds of Earth!

00:12:51.850 --> 00:12:54.580
Six Pack is now in the last position!

00:12:54.790 --> 00:12:56.630
Good luck, Earth-san!

00:12:57.290 --> 00:13:00.500
Come on, Earth. Come on, Kitasan!

00:13:00.500 --> 00:13:04.740
Entering the third corner for a second time,
and Kitasan Black still holds the lead.

00:13:04.740 --> 00:13:07.510
How will the horse girls in the
rest of the pack swap positions?

00:13:07.510 --> 00:13:09.240
She's running the way she always does.

00:13:09.240 --> 00:13:10.790
She certainly is.

00:13:10.790 --> 00:13:11.560
Yeah.

00:13:12.040 --> 00:13:13.850
Desperately, and with everything she has...

00:13:13.850 --> 00:13:17.310
The kinda running that
energizes you by watching it.

00:13:17.570 --> 00:13:19.970
Not slick, but so cool.

00:13:19.970 --> 00:13:21.960
That's Kitasan Black.

00:13:22.530 --> 00:13:26.890
Then in third place from the front is
Read Poetry, looking for the timing to attack.

00:13:26.890 --> 00:13:29.570
We might be looking at a war
of wills for the Arima Kinen!

00:13:30.540 --> 00:13:34.410
I want to win. I want to win. I want to win.

00:13:35.080 --> 00:13:39.420
I want to win. I want to win! I want to win!

00:13:39.420 --> 00:13:43.510
I want to win! I want to win! I want to win!

00:13:43.980 --> 00:13:47.680
I want to win! I want to win! I want to win!

00:13:47.960 --> 00:13:51.560
I want to win! I want to win! I want to win!

00:13:51.900 --> 00:13:56.170
I want to win! I want to win! I want to win!

00:13:56.170 --> 00:13:58.850
I want to win! I want to win!

00:14:45.610 --> 00:14:47.490
And there goes Kitasan Black!

00:14:47.490 --> 00:14:49.240
Pouring out every last drop she can muster,

00:14:49.240 --> 00:14:52.420
she launches forward, one step after another!

00:14:52.420 --> 00:14:54.030
Oh, no, you don't!

00:14:54.030 --> 00:14:55.620
Kitasan!

00:14:55.620 --> 00:14:57.450
Kitasan!

00:14:57.110 --> 00:15:00.460
Step after step after step after step...

00:15:00.460 --> 00:15:02.690
Kitasan Black is picking up the pace!

00:15:02.690 --> 00:15:04.380
Go!

00:15:02.900 --> 00:15:04.380
You can do this!

00:15:04.380 --> 00:15:05.250
Run!

00:15:05.250 --> 00:15:06.550
Go!

00:15:06.550 --> 00:15:10.520
Only a bit more to go as
the cheers shake Nakayama!

00:15:10.520 --> 00:15:12.460
This is so amazing! You can do it, Kitasan!

00:15:12.460 --> 00:15:15.260
Keep going! You're almost there!

00:15:15.260 --> 00:15:16.250
Get 'em.

00:15:18.770 --> 00:15:19.600
Kita-chan!

00:15:19.600 --> 00:15:21.060
Just keep going!

00:15:21.060 --> 00:15:23.280
I love seeing her run!

00:15:23.280 --> 00:15:24.440
It's so down to earth and desperate!

00:15:24.440 --> 00:15:25.810
Just like us!

00:15:25.810 --> 00:15:27.020
I can't not get psyched!

00:15:27.020 --> 00:15:28.320
You have to do it!

00:15:28.320 --> 00:15:29.420
She's so, so strong!

00:15:29.420 --> 00:15:30.700
Go! Go!

00:15:30.700 --> 00:15:32.900
You can do it, come on!

00:15:31.610 --> 00:15:34.010
Kitasan Black!

00:15:34.010 --> 00:15:36.200
The second place position is hotly contested!

00:15:36.200 --> 00:15:39.110
We can see Cheval Grand and
Ribon Etude from the outside!

00:15:39.110 --> 00:15:41.240
But just look at her! No one
can touch Kitasan Black!

00:15:41.240 --> 00:15:42.950
She's not letting anyone reach her shadow,

00:15:42.950 --> 00:15:45.980
with everyone staring at her back!

00:15:45.980 --> 00:15:47.130
With a two-length lead!

00:15:47.130 --> 00:15:48.250
Go!

00:15:48.250 --> 00:15:49.590
Go!

00:15:49.590 --> 00:15:50.840
Go!

00:15:59.850 --> 00:16:00.680
We are...

00:16:00.680 --> 00:16:04.840
witnessing a shooting star!

00:16:04.840 --> 00:16:06.820
Kitasan Black!

00:16:16.570 --> 00:16:19.820
And the Nakayama Racecourse erupts!

00:16:19.820 --> 00:16:22.580
A congratulatory roar in unison!

00:16:22.580 --> 00:16:26.330
Incredible! Kitasan Black was incredible!

00:16:26.580 --> 00:16:32.310
At the end of her long road, what awaited
her was congratulations and gratitude!

00:16:32.890 --> 00:16:39.700
You can see faces saying, "Thank you," and,
"You did it," throughout all the stands!

00:16:39.700 --> 00:16:46.140
Kitasan Black now has seven
G1 wins! One more for the road!

00:16:46.140 --> 00:16:48.570
Thank you! Thank you, Kitasan!

00:16:48.820 --> 00:16:50.560
You were awesome, Kitasan!

00:16:50.560 --> 00:16:53.320
I can keep going! I'm gonna
keep trying again, tomorrow!

00:16:53.320 --> 00:16:56.590
Kita-chan! Thank you!

00:17:06.180 --> 00:17:07.690
It's a festival.

00:17:10.030 --> 00:17:11.340
Seven G1 wins.

00:17:12.250 --> 00:17:14.920
She ended up a greater horse girl than me.

00:17:14.920 --> 00:17:18.340
I'm impressed. It's just like you predicted.

00:17:18.740 --> 00:17:21.350
She really is something.

00:17:21.930 --> 00:17:25.350
The dead heat for second place,
after a photo finish,

00:17:25.350 --> 00:17:27.360
has been confirmed as It's Calling.

00:17:27.360 --> 00:17:29.360
Third place is Cheval Grand.

00:17:29.810 --> 00:17:31.440
And as tough of a race as it was,

00:17:31.440 --> 00:17:35.360
in the end, Kitasan Black's
performance shone brightest!

00:17:35.620 --> 00:17:38.090
Crown-san finished 13th.

00:17:38.710 --> 00:17:39.940
Trainer-san.

00:17:39.940 --> 00:17:40.740
Yes?

00:17:41.210 --> 00:17:43.710
I want to resume training
at the beginning of the year

00:17:44.070 --> 00:17:46.170
with an eye towards the spring races.

00:17:47.500 --> 00:17:48.600
Understood.

00:17:49.880 --> 00:17:51.680
Right. I should run.

00:17:52.030 --> 00:17:56.760
Because I want to see the same
sight that Kita-chan just did.

00:17:57.180 --> 00:17:58.800
Earth did a good job!

00:17:58.800 --> 00:18:01.260
Seventh place. A quality showing.

00:18:01.470 --> 00:18:05.460
Those were some crazy cheers.
It even got us excited.

00:18:05.460 --> 00:18:09.710
Yes. A last run befitting of
such an incredible outpouring.

00:18:09.710 --> 00:18:12.050
To garner so much attention...

00:18:13.750 --> 00:18:16.810
Congratulations, Kitasan.

00:18:17.870 --> 00:18:19.330
She was strong.

00:18:19.330 --> 00:18:21.570
Yes. Much like she has been.

00:18:21.570 --> 00:18:24.970
No... that may have been her best race yet.

00:18:25.710 --> 00:18:29.220
It's a shame. She seems like
she could keep going to me.

00:18:29.220 --> 00:18:30.360
I wonder about that.

00:18:31.450 --> 00:18:35.760
To leave after this, in my opinion, would be
the most beautifully ephemeral choice.

00:18:36.320 --> 00:18:39.010
I guess she's your rival for a reason.

00:18:39.430 --> 00:18:40.140
She is.

00:18:40.650 --> 00:18:45.930
Kitasan! Kitasan! Kitasan!

00:18:43.850 --> 00:18:46.990
Whoa, and there's a Kitasan chant!

00:18:46.030 --> 00:19:10.410
Kitasan! Kitasan! Kitasan!

00:18:46.990 --> 00:18:49.330
She's waving back at the crowd in response!

00:18:49.330 --> 00:18:50.850
Kitasan Black!

00:21:16.040 --> 00:21:18.540
Tracen
Academy
Open
Campus

00:21:19.260 --> 00:21:20.410
Here you are.

00:21:21.400 --> 00:21:22.580
Here you are.

00:21:24.020 --> 00:21:25.210
Here you are!

00:21:25.210 --> 00:21:27.050
Thank you so much!

00:21:27.260 --> 00:21:30.290
Right, let me show you the pool next!

00:21:30.290 --> 00:21:31.390
Okay!

00:21:31.920 --> 00:21:34.480
Tracen Academy's known for both
its academic and sports programs.

00:21:36.490 --> 00:21:41.550
Impressive, right? It's the same
size as an actual racecourse.

00:21:51.740 --> 00:21:54.750
Team Spica

00:21:51.740 --> 00:21:54.750
\hJoin us or get
left in the mud

00:22:00.410 --> 00:22:01.850
There you are.

00:22:04.670 --> 00:22:09.090
Shine!! Team Capella!!

00:22:05.010 --> 00:22:06.320
What are you doing?

00:22:06.320 --> 00:22:08.010
Everyone's waiting.

00:22:08.010 --> 00:22:09.090
Come on.

00:22:10.180 --> 00:22:12.220
Let's go, Kita-chan!

00:22:12.500 --> 00:22:13.290
Yeah!

00:22:16.170 --> 00:22:17.890
What were you spacing out for?

00:22:17.890 --> 00:22:21.010
You can't start getting lazy just
because it's spring, y'know.

00:22:21.010 --> 00:22:23.340
I wonder what kind of horse
girls we'll see next?

00:22:23.340 --> 00:22:24.980
Good question!

